# Alpine AddressSanitizer / LeakSanitizer suppressions.
#
# Rules here should be RARE and well-justified.  Prefer fixing the root cause
# to adding a suppression.  Each entry must cite the reason the leak/error
# cannot be fixed here (third-party, false positive, intentional lifetime, etc.)
# and leave a trail for future reviewers.

# spdlog allocates its thread-local pattern formatter once and never releases
# it — that's not a leak, it's process-lifetime state.  Observed with
# sanitizer runs against Catch2 executables that use spdlog via base/AppUtils/Log.
leak:spdlog

# Catch2 keeps a global test registry that outlives main().  The allocations
# are bounded by the number of test cases compiled in; no runtime growth.
leak:Catch::Detail::unique_name
leak:Catch::getMutableRegistryHub

# asio internal scheduler uses a thread-local service registry.  The registry
# is cleaned up on thread exit only when ~io_context runs; tests that
# construct io_context on the stack do so correctly.
leak:asio::detail::service_registry
